<h1>Learning Resources Development Centre</h1><p>
	Located on the second floor of the trades wing of the Cranbrook campus, the LRDC provides a wide variety of services and support to trades students. The LRDC provides trades students access to study space, technology, equipment, media and print collections required in the trades programs at the College.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Hours of Operation:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Monday - Friday 8:00am - 3:30pm.</li>
	<li>
		Evening support/access to the LRDC is provided via the trade tool crib assistant(s)</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<small><strong>Note:</strong> hours of operation may vary during the course of the year due to statutory holidays, etc.</small></p>
<p>
	<strong>Student support provided by the LRDC:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		quiet study space</li>
	<li>
		tutorial space</li>
	<li>
		group meeting space</li>
	<li>
		exam writing services</li>
	<li>
		student registration/administrative support</li>
	<li>
		viewing videos required for the program</li>
	<li>
		access to a student computer(s) to facilitate student access to e-mail, computer based instructional materials, library catalogue, electronic resources, Internet, word processing, etc.</li>
	<li>
		drafting table</li>
	<li>
		photocopying</li>
</ul>

